        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 5:43PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 543 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Adrian, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Adrian, Palmyra, Fairfield, Jasper, Weston, Ogden Center, Sand Creek,
and Cadmus.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
